The paper discusses the optimization of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The focus is on designing an ultra-low power hardware accelerator, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET) and system-on-chip (SoC) integration (cs.SY). The use of binary weights in the CNN algorithm is also a key aspect of the paper, which relates to the field of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents results on energy efficiency and area efficiency, which could also be relevant to the field of computer architecture (cs.AR).
